HEADWORD: Micromere
<hw>Mi"cro*mere</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets>
+ <ets>-mere</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>One of the smaller
cells, or blastomeres, resulting from the complete segmentation of a
telolecithal ovum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

